                     fill="none"
                     stroke-width="1.2"
                     stroke-linecap="round"
                     stroke-linejoin="round"
                     stroke="#88D8FF"
                     xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                    <!-- Box -->
                    <path d="M3 7L12 3L21 7V17L12 21L3 17V7Z" />
                    <!-- Box Lid -->
                    <path d="M3 7L12 11L21 7" />
                    <!-- Cushioning inside -->
                    <circle cx="8" cy="14" r="1.5" />
                    <circle cx="12" cy="16" r="1.5" />
                    <circle cx="16" cy="14" r="1.5" />
                </svg>

            </span>
            <h4>4. Secure Packaging</h4>
            <p>
                Package the items you’re selling in a sturdy shipping box that fits items. You can use bubble wrap, cushioning foam, plastic grocery bags, or newspaper to cushion the interior of the box so the contents do not get damaged in shipping. Scrap pieces of cardboard can be used to reinforce the box. Be sure items will be secure and not move around during shipping.
            </p>
            <div class="shine"></div>
            <div class="background">
                <div class="tiles">
                    <div class="tile tile-1"></div>
                    <div class="tile tile-2"></div>
                    <div class="tile tile-3"></div>
                    <div class="tile tile-4"></div>

                    <div class="tile tile-5"></div>
